# Repository Management

Repositories are the fundamental unit on GitHub. Every codebase, issue tracker, wiki, and Actions pipeline lives inside a repository. The GitHub API provides full CRUD access to repos, including creation, configuration, forking, and deletion.

## Creating a Repository

```javascript
import { Octokit } from "@octokit/rest";

const octokit = new Octokit({ auth: process.env.GITHUB_TOKEN });

// Create a user-owned repo
const { data: repo } = await octokit.repos.createForAuthenticatedUser({
  name: "my-project",
  description: "A new project",
  private: false,
  auto_init: true,
});
console.log(repo.html_url, repo.clone_url);

// Create an org-owned repo
const { data: orgRepo } = await octokit.repos.createInOrg({
  org: "my-org",
  name: "shared-lib",
  description: "Shared library",
  private: true,
});
```

## Cloning and Forking

```bash
# Clone via HTTPS
git clone https://github.com/owner/repo.git

# Clone via SSH
git clone git@github.com:owner/repo.git
```

```javascript
// Fork a repository
const { data: fork } = await octokit.repos.createFork({
  owner: "upstream-owner",
  repo: "upstream-repo",
});
```

## Repository Settings

```javascript
// Update repo settings
await octokit.repos.update({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  default_branch: "main",
  has_issues: true,
  has_wiki: false,
  allow_squash_merge: true,
  allow_merge_commit: false,
  allow_rebase_merge: true,
  delete_branch_on_merge: true,
});
```

## Branch Protection

```javascript
// Set branch protection rules
await octokit.repos.updateBranchProtection({
  owner: "my-org",
  repo: "my-project",
  branch: "main",
  required_status_checks: {
    strict: true,
    contexts: ["ci/test", "ci/lint"],
  },
  enforce_admins: true,
  required_pull_request_reviews: {
    required_approving_review_count: 1,
  },
  restrictions: null,
});
```

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Purpose |
|----------|----------|
| `GITHUB_TOKEN` | Personal access token or installation token |
| `GITHUB_ORG` | Target organization (optional) |
